Node.Notes: (SYNTAX) Preposition plus infinitive would be expected syntactical construction here; the participle is unusual as ADV.
Unusual construction: "I weep with fasting with respect to my soul." Many change to "I humble my soul/myself with fasting" (in part on basis of ancient versions).
Either "[I am] the songs of the ones drinking strong drink" or "the songs of the ones drinking strong drink [mock at me]."
Apparently, shaking of the head from side to side as an expression of condolence/sympathy.
Literally "poison." Many follow LXX with "gall," also reflected in application to Jesus in Gospels. Perhaps poison is figuratively for bitter poison, leading to gall.
Probably refers to sacrificial feast at the Temple.
Uncertain. Apparently, "to those who are at peace for a trap." Some follow Aramaic Targum wth "sacrificial feasts" and others follow LXX with "for retribution."
A reference to a full-grown bull with "bull with horns [and] hoofs."
